ls that are unbounded and unreliable. We presented a backward reachability algorithm which, starting from a set of “bad” states, checks whether there is a backward path to the initial state of the system. Using standard techniques, the reachability algorithm can be used to check safety properties for lossy channel systems.</abstract></paper>